  223: {
    beginner: `Data Dredging = The misuse of data analysis to find patterns in data that can be presented as statistically significant.`,
    detail: `Data Dredging

Description:
The misuse of data analysis to find patterns in data that can be presented as statistically significant.
If you torture the data long enough, it will confess.

Example (question)
« Testing many hypotheses until one fits. »
This is the exact kind of move the question is testing.

Example (everyday)
The argument tests many hypotheses and only reports the one that looks successful by chance.
The same logic shows up even when the surface story changes.

How it works
The argument uses the surface clue as if it were enough to settle the claim.

So:
- Looking hard enough guarantees finding a coincidence.
- The hypothesis must be chosen before the test.
- P-hacking creates false scientific breakthroughs.

Key concept inside it
P-hacking:
The misuse of data analysis to find patterns in data that can be presented as statistically significant.

Why it matters
Explains why:
- Looking hard enough guarantees finding a coincidence.
- The hypothesis must be chosen before the test.
- P-hacking creates false scientific breakthroughs.

The uncomfortable implication
You can prove anything if you hide all the failed experiments.

One-line version
Data Dredging = The misuse of data analysis to find patterns in data that can be presented as statistically significant.`,
  },
